    BROOKFIELD, WIS., March 11 - <seller>Rexnord Inc</seller> said it signed a
<status>definitive agreement</status> to sell its <acquired>Railway Maintenance Equipment
Co</acquired> subsidiary to <purchaser>Oak Industries Inc</purchaser>. Terms were withheld.
    Also participating in the agreement was Banner Industries
Inc, which previously agreed to acquire <sellerabr>Rexnord</sellerabr>.
    <acqabr>Railway Maintenance</acqabr> had 1986 sales of 16 mln dlrs.
    <sellerabr>Rexnord</sellerabr> said the sale is part of a major program to divest
several of its businesses representing about 200 mln dlrs in
net assets. Still to be divested are the Process Machinery
Division with sales of 137 mln dlrs and Mathews Conveyer Co,
with sales of 83 mln dlrs. -- Corrects mame of purchaser
